      "note_no": "108",
      "note": "In classical Arabic, as in ancient Hebrew usage, the term ab (\"father\") was applied not only to the direct male parent but also to grandfathers and even more distant ancestors, as well as to paternal uncles: which explains why Ishmael, who was Jacob's uncle, is mentioned in this context. Since he was the first-born of Abraham's sons, his name precedes that of Isaac."
